<title>SPAIN: S&amp;P rates Canary Islands long-term govt debt &quot;AA&quot;.</title>
<headline>S&amp;P rates Canary Islands long-term govt debt &quot;AA&quot;.</headline>
<dateline>MADRID 1997-02-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ratings agency Standard &amp; Poor's said on Thursday it assigned an &quot;AA&quot; rating to Spain's Canary Islands long-term regional government debt.</p>
<p>It rated its outlook stable.</p>
<p>In a note, S&amp;P's said the rating reflected a solid and stable financial situation and a very low level of debt.</p>
<p>It also reflected an economy highly concentrated in tourism and a special fiscal regime that gives the Canary Islands the flexibility of extra income.</p>
<p>-- Madrid Newsroom +341 585 2160</p>
</text>
